  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Commodity Communities of Change: Cotton</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Solidaridad was re-elected for another four-year term to the Council (board) of the Better Cotton Initiative in June 2018. With Solidaridad&#x2019;s representative (Isabelle Roger) being one of the only two women on the board. The attention of the board was brought on improving gender equality in the board. We also put on the agenda the topic of inclusion of smallholder farmers in Brazil (currently de facto excluded), which is dependent on the agreement between BCI and the national cotton producer association (ABRAPA). We also contributed to the discussion on the revision of the BCI verification procedures towards a process more geared towards continuous improvement than certification.</narrative>
  </description>
